description:
Overview

The writer of the Academy Award-winning film RAY ends his new series at Boom! with a bang! What will be the final fate of Lincoln "Linc" Greer and his son? Find out in the shocking ending to this critically acclaimed mini-series.

Overview

Mike Kane's been keeping busy - going to high school, drinking beer with his buddies... and hiding the fact that he's a werewolf. An average kid from a single parent home's discovering that his taste for flesh and violence is... In The Blood. What's happening to Mike? And how long will he be able to keep the change hidden?
name: One-Shot

description:
Overview

The big finale! The showdown comes to a head, as Jeremiah faces off against Dak Moira over the Basal Shard, a fragment of the original matter that caused the Big Bang! Dak's plan for cosmic suicide is finally revealed! This is a war, not just for the fate of the earth, but for the fate of the entire universe – and it lies in the hands of an escaped criminal, Jeremiah Harm!

Overview

Former agent Eric Westfall has been called out of his perfect suburban retirement, complete with wife and kid, to recover an agent gone rogue.

He has to stop his target from auctioning a stolen hard-drive, chock full of classified info, on the black market for $50 million. His mission - turn the target back into a loyal agent for the government, or kill them.

But things get complicated when it's revealed that Westfall has been called back to duty specifically because he has history with his target - romantic history.  Will he be able to take down Emma, his ex-lover?
name: Left On Mission... And Revenge

description:
Overview

Eric Westfall continues his search for Emma, with the secrets of one of America's biggest intelligence agencies hanging in the balance.

Tracked by Painter, an agent tasked to ensure that Westfall kills or turns Emma, Westfall finds his mark - but not in any way that he could have predicted...
name: Ibizan Nights

description:
Eric Westfall's mission remains just out of reach. Having found Emma, is he now in over his head? Can he talk her into coming back, or is it all over before it's even begun?

What's more - what's the big secret that Emma's willing to die for? And can Westfall keep the agency at bay and Agent Painter from killing him in the field?
name: Interludes

description:
Overview

Westfall reaches Morocco as he searches for Emma. Painter is there, hindering his every move. While Emma prepares to finally sell her information, Westfall desperately tries to stop her - and save her soul. The penultimate chapter in this spy-thriller!
name: Panoramic View

description: It's all over. Eric catches up with Emma, but is he too late? As she meets the Russians to create the transaction, will the agency kill her to prevent their secrets from getting out? Can Eric save Emma before she imperils herself and the entire western world?
name: The Sema and the Damage Done

description: When a scientist succeeds in creating an Artificial Intelligence, he discovers to his horror that the government plans on making it a weapon. On the run, he hides the program inside a mechanical toy bear. An unsuspecting family buys the toy bear and a little boy discovers a new best friend he never knew he had – a cute, cuddly toy bear who's got all the moves of James Bond!

Overview

In the tradition of Cthulhu Tales and Zombie Tales! Everyone loves a good ninja now and again, so BOOM! turns its attention to these practitioners of the ancient Asian stealthy arts. From comedy, to drama, to action, this anthology features familiar BOOM! writers like John (Transformers: the Movie) Rogers, Johanna (Eureka) Stokes, Andrew (X Isle, Eureka) Cosby, Michael Alan (Second Wave, X Isle) Nelson, with the new addition of CSI screenwriter Henry Alonzo Myers! Featuring art from Ron (Thanos) Lim, Chris (Eberron: Eye of the Wolf) Lie, Chee (Second Wave), and more! Cover by Eisner Award-winning legend Dave Johnson!

Stories:

  • Smoke and Mirrors
  • Unsheathed
  • Ninja School Dropout
  • Desert Sun
  • Special Needs Ninjas
name: Ninja Tales

description:
1. "The Joy-Bringers!" (Superman and Batman) written by Cary Burkett, penciled by Irv Novick, inked by Frank Chiaramonte, colored by Carl Gafford and lettered by Ben Oda.
  2. "No Title" (Green Arrow and Black Canary) written by Mike W. Barr, penciled and inked by Gil Kane, colored by Tom Ziuko and lettered by John Costanza.
  3. "Doctor Katar and Mister Plert" (Hawkman) written by Bob Rozakis, penciled by Carmine Infantino, inked by Rodin Rodriguez, colored by Jerry Serpe and lettered by Philip Felix.
  4. "Charity Begins..." (Captain Marvel, Captain Marvel Jr., Mary Marvel and Kid Eternity) written by E. Nelson Bridwell, penciled and inked by Gil Kane, colored by Adrienne Roy and lettered by Ben Oda.

Notes:

  • Last 48 page issue.
  • Stun Arrow and Knockout Gas Arrow used.
  • First DC Comics appearances of Her Highness and Silk.
  • The last Captain Marvel feature in World's Finest Comics. The Captain Marvel series continues in Adventure Comics #491.
name: The Joy-Bringers! / No Title / Doctor Katar and Mister Plert / Charity Begins...

description:
1. The Super-Pranks of Krypto! (Superboy) written by Jerry Siegel, art by George Papp
  2. My Favorite Gal (Sue : gag page)
  3. New Stars for Old Glory public service message written by Jack Schiff
  4. Aquaman Meets Aquagirl! (Aquaman) written by Robert Bernstein, art by Ramona Fradon. Reprinted in: Super DC Giant #S-26, Aquaman Archives #1, Showcase Presents Aquaman #1
  5. I'm Going to Run Away from Home (Little Pete) gag page by Henry Boltinoff
  6. The Case of the Vanishing Arrows! (Green Arrow) written by Robert Bernstein, art by Lee Elias. Reprinted in: World's Finest Comics #143, Super-Team Family #2, Showcase Presents Green Arrow #1
    What stuff is Green Arrow making his new arrows out of, and why do they keep disappearing?
  7. Movie Mirth (gag strip)
name: The Super-Pranks of Krypto!

description: Also includes activity and puzzle pages.
name: The Lone Ranger : The Hidden Loot

description:
Title is a Dutch translation of "Panthro Stands Alone!"

Cover is a reprint of Marvel's Thundercats #3
name: Panthro Staat Alleen!

description:
Gezocht in English means "Wanted"

Cover reprinted from Marvel's Thundercats #4
name: Gezocht

description:
Overview

Sci Fi's Galactica series writer Kevin Fahey - joined this issue by co-writer Clay Carmouche - is back and joined by artist Jonathan Lau for a special "origin" series focusing on Kara and Helo! From the academy to their assignment onboard the Galactica, follow the previously untold tale in Dynamite's "Origin" series!
name: Starbuck & Helo - Part 2 of 3

description: The City of Light is just beyond the reach of the Liandra and her son, Jude. To get there requires a leap of faith that may well be beyond the abilities of a fallen angel and a disenfranchised priest. But if they cannot overcome their own fears, then Bete Noire will remain in Moloch's hands and the world will spiral into darkness.

The war for Bete Noire is over... and it hasn't turned out the way anyone expected. Now the losers are on the run, the victors are hoping to eradicate them, and the race is on to find the one thing that can turn around the outcome.

The battle for Bete Noire is at hand! In an epic climax of a story building for more than two years, the defenders of The City that Shapes the World face off against an incursion by the forces of the Hierarchy, with the fate of the entire city at stake! An anniversary issue with a stunning wraparound cover by series artist J.K. Woodward and ten pages of special features, including galleries, interviews and more.
As war continues to ravage Bete Noire, and with Jude the Magistrate taken captive, the Fallen Angel races the clock to try and find her missing son before the power of Bete Noire is usurped.
name: Red Horse Riding, Part 2

description: War has come thundering through Bete Noire. An ancient evil in the demonic person of Gills De Rais has come to the city that shapes the world, and he doesn't seem interested in leaving anytime soon. Alliances will shift, lives will be lost... and if the Fallen Angel is unable to stop the fall of Bete Noire, then the rest of the world may well be next.
name: Red Horse Riding, Part 1

description: In a world where superheroes are merely four-color creations of comic books, a small boy tries to convince his friends about his amazing adventure in a mysterious city that he inadvertently slept-walked into... a city where he would have most certainly died if not for the intervention of a real-life superhero called the Fallen Angel.

The Collector, the man who just employed S with a new task, tells him that people who are too sensitive goes crazy. And in top of that, he's tasked with a mission that's capable of tearing "S" Usual Calmess apart... Will "The Stooge" Be Capable to put this job off?

Also. He gets drunk on a bathtub while thiking of life, and Luna (as pictured in the cover) Blows her ktichen sky-high when some goons are tracking "the stuff" Down. Paul Pope's Heavy Liquid it's as crazy as it gets!
name: Issue #2

description: "The Stooge" is trying to find secrets behind the job he was offered to do. The Reason? The person he's looking for has retired 5 years ago, although she's not a total Stranger in S's Life. Enter a guy in a white hat with a 50.000 Volt pinch that kills at the very contact. A hotel room... Handcuffs and lots of lipstick...
name: Issue #3

description: Jude, the new magistrate of Bete Noire, is faced with the hard truth that being in charge of the city that shapes the world is not remotely what he expected, and the five stages of grief are played out in a single, traumatic day.
name: The Five Stages Of Jude

description: "S" Travels from New York to Paris in half an hour, using some sort of bizarre airplane. Then, we discover S's skills to speak french (he's better speaking any language in the world but french) So he has a strange machine with him that translates from french o english and from english to french... Meanwhile, he reaches the subject he was looking for, so he arrvies with a present, a dozen red roses for her... Some questions get asked, some questions get answered!
name: Issue #4

description: The exciting conclusion to the two-part tale guest-starring Billy Tucci's popular character, Shi! Hidden away in an ancient land, there is a city of ghosts with a demented leader who desires to spread his city's influence across the globe. The last time that happened, Europe was afflicted with the Black Plague. Get ready for a recurrence... unless the Fallen Angel and Shi are able to prevent it.

Concluding the previously untold tale of the Fallen Angel's predecessor. The mysterious Lin has arrived in the city of Bete Noire and become an absolute force for good. But absolute power—even for good—corrupts absolutely. Will Lin fall from grace, or prove to be a super girl?

Though it cannot be stated outright in the story for legal reasons, the character of Lin is Linda Danvers, the lead character in Peter David's Supergirl run. When Fallen Angel originally launched at DC, it was often implied that Lee was actually Linda, and many of the series' themes were continued from previous Supergirl stories.
When asked to comment about Lin, Peter David said "Can I say this is Linda Danvers? Of course I can't. However, it's pretty freaking obvious that it is."

New York Times Best-selling author Peter David presents a stand-alone tale of the Fallen Angel, wherein Lee discovers "The Predecessor." The special issue features guest-art and cover courtesy of Kristian Donaldson (Supermarket, DMZ).

Though it cannot be stated outright in the story for legal reasons, the character of Lin is Linda Danvers, the lead character in Peter David's Supergirl run. When Fallen Angel originally launched at DC, it was often implied that Lee was actually Linda, and many of the series' themes were continued from previous Supergirl stories.

When asked to comment about Lin, Peter David said "Can I say this is Linda Danvers? Of course I can't. However, it's pretty freaking obvious that it is."

An elderly man finds strange and bizarre dreams driving him to Bete Noire... dreams of himself as a younger man with strange powers, aiding desperate people in need of help. Are they pure fantasy? Or is he recalling a life that once was his, and is now forgotten? Only the Fallen Angel may hold the key to the answers.

Though it cannot be stated outright in the story for legal reasons, the character of Lin is Linda Danvers, the lead character in Peter David's Supergirl run. When Fallen Angel originally launched at DC, it was often implied that Lee was actually Linda, and many of the series' themes were continued from previous Supergirl stories.
When asked to comment about Lin, Peter David said "Can I say this is Linda Danvers? Of course I can't. However, it's pretty freaking obvious that it is."

Buffy Summers appears on a tv playing a scene from the Buffy The Vampire Slayer episde "Normal Again".

Witness the conclusion of the trial of Asia Minor, as Jude holds in his hand the power of life and death over Bete Noire's favorite drug dealer...and must decide whether to use it. And, if he does decide to execute Asia Minor for his crimes...will the Fallen Angel stand by and let it happen?

When a new designer drug threatens to unleash a literal plague upon Bete Noire, Jude considers using vicious tactics upon the drug's source, Asia Minor... tactics that the Fallen Angel must prevent him from using.
name: The Long Seduction of Jude, Part 1

description: When a new designer drug threatens to unleash a literal plague upon Bete Noire, Jude considers using vicious tactics upon the drug's source, Asia Minor... tactics that the Fallen Angel must prevent him from using.
name: The Long Seduction of Jude, Part 1

description: A haunting tale as a dying, blind singer seeks to avert his impending death by looking for a miracle... A miracle that's known as the Fallen Angel.
name: A Sad Song for Jerry May

description: In this issue, a mysterious woman from the Fallen Angel's past, continues her holy war against the city of Bete Noire in hopes of bringing about world peace. Only JJ Sachs stands between her and her goal, but should she be with her or against her and will JJ live to find out?
name: Holy War, Part 2: Ayr

description: Jude faces the first major test of his power over Bete Noire as a religious war breaks out in the city. And with the Fallen Angel out of town and unable to help him, he turns to the only individuals who may be able to get things under control-the inimitable Sachs & Violens.

This special standalone issue presents a haunting tale of death and redemption, as a dying, blind singer seeks to avert his impending demise by looking for a miracle... a miracle that's known as the Fallen Angel.

You're an angel and you've just monumentally pissed off God. Stripped of your wings and pretty much everything else, you're sent hurtling to Earth and crash land in a desert, where you're found unconscious by passing Arab nomads. How do you handle what happens next? Come up with your own answer, and then compare it to that of Lee, the Fallen Angel.

This is the issue that Fallen Angel fans have been waiting for. The final showdown - and we do mean final - between the Fallen Angel and Doctor Juris for control of Bete Noire, with the fate of their son hanging in the balance.

Overview

The kids have found nothing but hardship and near-death in the post-apocalyptic landscape...in a brief respite in the wilderness, they take the opportunity to reflect on the new world order. Featuring the third chapter of the Marc "Backlash" Slayton backup story, by Christos Gage and Mike McKone!
name: Teenage Wasteland, Part 3 - What Did You Want To Be When The World Blew Up?

description:
Dynamite continues to present the most the most savage stories that comic creators have ever told! Each issue of the bi-monthly Savage Tales will feature a rotating cast of characters and creators featuring the savage and brutal worlds of Red Sonja, Thulsa Doom and more!

Issue #7 Features:

• Red Sonja By Vito Delsante and Lui Antonio: an all-new Red Sony short by regular series writer Brian Reed!

• Hercules: The Unnamed Task (Part 2) By Doug Murray and Fabiano Neves; History tells us of the 12 Tasks of Hercules, but writer Doug Murray and artist Fabiano Neves continue to tell us of the very first, untold task of the legendary demi-god!

• Thulsa Doom: Age of Doom (Part 3) By Luke Lieberman and Noah Salonga; concluding the explosive origin of Red Sonja villain Thulsa Doom!

•Quartermain (Part 1) -- A new adventure featuring the dynamite tales of the legendary adventurer! Written by Entourage writer Matt Wolpert!

All the action and excitement (and sex and violence) under two "savage" covers, one by Stjepan Sejic and the other from artist Fabiano Neves
name: Memento Mori Part One / Pillars of Hercules Part Two / Quatermain Part One / Thulsa Doom: The Serpent's Den Part Three

description:
The Savage Tales from DYNAMITE ENTERTAINMENT continue in issue #8! This month, Red Sonja and Quatermain continue! Plus: the return of the Hunter from the pages of Red Sonja and the return of Savage Tales Atlantis!

Red Sonja (part 2) By Vito Delsante and Lui Antonio: the conclusion of an all-new Red Sonja short!

Quartermain (Part 2) By Luke Lieberman, Matt (Entourage) Wolpert and Diego Bernard: The early adventures of the world-s greatest explorer continue to unfold.

The Trials of Osin (Part 1) by Luke Lieberman and Fabiano Neves: From the pages of Red Sonja come the untold trials of Osin, bridging the gap from the end of the Gath storyline and the bold new direction begun in Red Sonja #35!

Battle For Atlantis (Part 1) By Leah Moore, John Reppion and Pablo Marcos: the fan-favorite Savage Tales series returns with an all-new sequel serial!

All the action and excitement (and sex and violence) under one incredible cover by Arthur Suydam!
name: Memento Mori Part Two / Battle for Atlantis Act II Part I: Island of Death / Quatermain Part Two / Osin Part One

description:
A little girl dead. By his hand. A line the Punisher swore he'd never cross. Now the hooded men who have been preying on the little Mexican town have something more to worry about. Frank Castle has never had less to lose...or more pain to dole out.

Frank Castle, The Punisher has been asked by the people of a mexican farming town to get rid of a group of murderers who have been terrozing the poor community and kidnapping its women. Frank has started this mission fast and hard. He has killed several enemies already, but hes hit a snag. hes made one big mistake. Upon opening fire wildly in a rumored drug cartel, he discovers, to his shock , a little girl, dead at his feet. The Punisher is in for one hell of a Reality check. one that could mean the end for the vengeful killer.

Summary (spoilers alert)

Frank has killed a 6 year old girl in the assault of an abandoned warehouse, believed to be a drug cartel. He returns to the little girls family , and tells them he killed their daughter. They immediately persecute him and cast him out of their village. He takes the child's body and carries it gently over a hill to the cometary, as the sun sets in front of him.He leaves Her family and friends to grieve in peace. Frank returns to his rundown apartment, and contemplates death to the guilty - himself. The kidnapped women are now used as slaves by Franks unknown enemy. One of them threatens her captor with a blade, but she is thrown into a closet, and a masked ,heavy set man tries to rape her.He is stopped by a superior. Frank almost commits suicide, but suffers a flashback of his family's death, and realizes he has to be sure he is guilty of murder, before he joins them. He returns to the child's grave, and hesitantly removes the spent rounds from her flesh. The bullets are 22. caliber, not his 45.s. He is not guilty of the child's death. Frank assaults an informant for the information on his next target, who tells him he is merely a trucker looking for whatever work he could get. Franks enemies payed him to set up the scene to look like Frank killed the child. Frank begins to torture him with his knife.Later, Frank is reloading his guns, and gathers his emotions. With his head back in the game, he continues his endless mission.
name: She is Dead

description: Inspired by TRON, Disney’s groundbreaking science-fiction motion picture classic, TRON: GHOST IN THE MACHINE takes place in present day, over two decades after the events of the film. Jet Bradley, son of the original TRON programmer Alan Bradley, has recently escaped the computer world. But his experiences within cyberspace have left him emotionally scarred - vivid nightmares plague him, and he’s become paranoid and unstable. He shuns technology wherever possible, leaving him effectively crippled in the modern world. And now something within the computer world wants him back. Exploring the fast-paced action from the hit film and video game, plus the impact of experiencing the cyberworld on the human psyche, TRON: GHOST IN THE MACHINE starts a thrilling new chapter in the TRON saga.

volume.name: Tron: The Ghost in the Machine

description: Includes the first part of Just Us, Justice Ducks adaptation.
name: The Volcano of Gold!

volume.name: Disney's Aladdin - The Official Movie Adaptation

description:
It’s the “season premiere” of one of last year’s Pilot Season winners! You voted for it, you got it! From the pages of Marc Silvestri’s Cyberforce comes a solo series for Cyblade!

Set in the days before she joined Cyberforce, Dominique Thiebaut has been leading a double life. By day she’s an awkward teenager, but at night, a chip in her brain changes her into the deadly master assassin Cyblade. With the ability to create psychic blades of energy, she’s an expert in everything from thieving to assassination, performing industrial espionage for the seemingly benevolent Cyberdata corporation. But with the help of a spy sent to infiltrate the company, Cyblade has broken free from Cyberdata’s control. She must find a way to escape from their clutches for good, all the while trying to discover who she really is beneath.
name: Part 1: Waking Life

description: 3 thrilling tales of the Spirit! "The Most Important Meal," "Force of Arms" and "Gossip and Gertrude Granch" are all written by Alan Moore, with art & lettering by Dave Gibbons. Plus: "The Spirit vs. Sam 'Slippery' Eall," a classic Spirit splash page by Will Eisner from November 30, 1947. Also: 3-page feature "The Many Origins of the Spirit" written by Catherine Garnier.

Funky Flashman's agreed to help Mister Miracle resume his stage career with a show at Madison Square Garden. Unfortunately, Manga Khan and the Cluster were able to get some tickets.

Notes:

  • A 48 page issue.
  • Indica title is Justice League Special 1.
  • A Mister Miracle robot appears.
  • On page 27 panel 1 a Babar the Movie advertisement appears on a taxi cab.
name: The Show Must Go On...And On... And On... And On

description: The spotlight is on the Huntress as, with a little help from her friends in the JLA (including Martian Manhunter, Blue Beetle, Fire & Ice), she tries to get her life in order. There's one hitch in her plan, however, and that's the Hunter, the newest costumed vigilante on the streets...and under the Hunter's mask is Sal, Helena's ex-bodyguard. Now it's up to her to find out exactly which side of the law he's on.
name: Burning Bridges

description:
When Elongated Man and Sue Dibny are taken hostage by the Royal Flush Gang, the Justice League reunites to rescue them in "Team Work".

Ralph and Sue Dibny are at the grand opening of Funny Stuff Park in Florida, with a large group of ambassadors from the United Nations, when the Royal Flush Gang attacks and hold everyone hostage in the Alice in Wonderland Castle. Booster Gold and Blue Beetle hear the distress call and with the aid of Fire and Ice fly in The Bug to save the ambassadors.

Superman who also hears the distress call flies from Metropolis and gets there first. The Royal Flush Gang, hinting that they are sponsored by someone very powerful, are prepared for the man of steel and are able to subdue him.

When Booster and Beetle’s team show up they are beaten back by the Royal Flush Gang and are forced to call in reinforcements, Power Girl, Metamorpho and Guy Gardner. The Royal Flush gang is prepared for them too, revealing that there benefactor is the Weapons Master and he wants Guy’s Green Lantern Ring.

Guy is quickly knocked out and Ice is forced to use the ring to communicate with Hal Jordan, who arrives on the scene with Wally West, Crimson Fox, Aquaman and Dr. Light. They are able to free Superman, and stop the Royal Flush Gang.

Superman, who was previously against joining the Justice League, is convinced by Hal that he is truly need and that the League needs to survive.

Notes:

  • Homage to Sugar and Spike as giant characters leading into the Funny Stuff amusement park.
  • Homage to Nutsy Squirrel as a character in the Funny Stuff amusement park.
  • Homage to Peter Porkchops with the Peter Porkchops Castle.
  • Homage to the comic book series Funny Stuff as the name of the amusement park.
  • In this issue there is references to Elongated Man #4, Justice League Europe #36, Justice League Quarterly #5 and Green Lantern #22.
name: Teamwork

description: The mysterious costumed figure first hit the streets of Metropolis in Superman #60 and even the Man of Steel couldn't get a handle on him. Now he's back in the pages of this one-shot special! While Agent Liberty seems to share Superman's agenda, his motives and methods - and those of the secret organization for which he works - are somewhat suspect. Now it's time to learn Agent Liberty's origins and see his secrets revealed.
name: Disgrace!
Endings and Beginnings

description: Debuting way back in 1944's MISS AMERICA MAGAZINE, Patsy Walker starred in a multitude of "soap opera" and "humor" titles through the late '60s, at which point Stan Lee brought her into the Marvel Universe with a cameo in FANTASTIC FOUR ANNUAL #3. Since her first appearance, the energetic and upbeat character has been many things, teen idol, super hero, even satanic bride, but now she's back from the great beyond and just wants to lead a quiet life. But the former Avenger and Defender will discover that she's become the prize in a hell-spawned contest which threatens to spill over into the earthy plane! She's young... she's undead... she kicks demon booty! Move over Buffy, here comes Hellcat!
name: An Avenger Reborn

description: From carnival roustabout to petty thief to troublemaking hero, one thing about ex-Avenger and Thunderbolt Clint Barton has never changed: he's a sucker for a lost cause. His travels in search of the world's best chili take Hawkeye out of spandex and into the real world problems of real world losers. Call HAWKEYE the ongoing series, ”hard-boiled fiction with an adrenaline kick” - Elmore Leonard meets John Woo! Exotic locations, offbeat characters, sleazy morals and sleazier motives … and a hero who's not afraid to get his hands dirty...
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 1: The Hotter, the Better

description: A weekend trip to Myrtle Beach. A stripper running away from a tough guy. A vagabond Clint Barton getting involved. The Avenging Archer’s new ongoing series continues! Will stirring this beehive of life's losers lead Hawkeye to solving the problem … or will it get him stung?
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 2: Hits & Mrs.

description: From a simple barroom rough-up in Myrtle Beach to beating up Cuban thugs in a Miami elevator, someone is going to a whole lot of trouble to keep the mystery of the ‘Unity Tattoo’ exactly that. Clint Barton has already gone from intrigued to annoyed … the next step is angry … and then anyone in his way better watch out!
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 3: Rat-A-Tat-Tat

description:
First issue.
Issues aren't numbered continuously, this is number 0 of 1990
name: The Chaos Coin Catastrophe!

description:
This first volume is based on the childhood of Marji Satrapi, and her personal point of view of political and social changes during and after the Islamic Revolution. This allows the reader to understand not only how this affected the main character and her family, but also how a society is forced to change in order to survive.

Another important event is the war between Iran and Irak and is precisely this war, the sum of tragedies around her and the strengthen of the Islamic government what forces the Satrapi family to send her precious daughter to Austria and end a vital chapter of her life.
name: The Story of a Childhood

description: Hawkeye's Myrtle Beach mystery spirals out of Clint's control just as the little Southern secret worth hundreds of millions of dollars was coming into focus. What was the "Unity Pact" that bound a group of Vietnam vets together and is the answer still a world away in Laos? The only way for Clint and a motley band of misfits to find out might be to go on a little road trip...
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 4: Like a Hole in the Head

description: A temple in Laos protected by 100 Archers. A thirty-year-old secret uncovered. A multi-billion dollar payday revealed. The fate of modern civilization as we know it depends on Clint Barton. Pray for us.
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 5: For Your Sins

description: The secret of the Unity stands revealed as Clint throws down against 99 archers out to protect a secret that could change the world - a secret that Hawkeye must possess!
name: The High, Hard Shaft, Part 6: Resurrection

description: When a beloved Brooklyn neighborhood deli owner is murdered, Clint Barton wants justice, leading Hawkeye on a trail of Russian mobsters, former KGB assassins, big secrets, a very old friend... and a very big surprise!
name: A Little Murder, Part 1

description: For the Avenging Archer, "A Little Murder" means a LOT of trouble! How do you say "WMD" in Russian? Clint better learn fast, because while he's hunting down a long-lost secret of the Afghani/Russian war, a KGB assassin with a rocket in his pocket is hunting him down. An old acquaintance is neck-deep in the mess, as well...but will she turn out to be friend or foe?
name: A Little Murder, Part 2
The Little Mermaid:Ariel and the Lobster's Loot
Rescue Rangers:Haunted Mouses; Darkwing Duck:In A Picnic Is No Picnic; The Marvelous World of Disney; Goof Troop:Wooly Bully

description: Just when the Foolkiller and the Punisher appear to have the upper hand in their war with the vicious hate-crime organization known as the White Angels, another player steps onto the field. Sickle Moon -- 98 pounds of bad, bad news.
name: “GOOD NIGHT, MOON”

description:
"Search for a Hero" continues as Robin tries to save one young boy from drowning in the tidal wave of gang warfare drenching a newly anarchic Gotham City. But why does Ragman not want the boy to be saved? And why is Spoiler paying a visit to the General?

During a protest of the arrests of Officers Wise and Cavallo, Scarab appears and begins shooting the crowd.  Robin shows up and gets Scarab away from the crowd, which also allows her to escape.

At school, Tim finds the place half empty.  He hasn't seen Spoiler for two days but does see some gang members selling drugs in the bathrooms.  He knows something needs to be done. 

Meanwhile Spoiler is being held by the General, who is patching up her gunshot wound after he shot her.  He tells her his plans to become Robin's main adversary.  Spoiler uses her charm and fists to escape.

Robin is still at a loss of how to deal with all the violence in Gotham.  He takes out the Batmobile to try to put some fear out there.  He soon comes across a new member of the Golden Dragons going by the name Lynx.  Not afraid of Batman in the Batmobile, she calls him out.  Robin has no choice but to use the riot control guns that shoot rubber bullets.  As he prepares to use them, Scarab shoots the road away from around the Batmobile.  Robin has to reveal himself and ejects out of the Batmobile when Scarab starts using real bullets on the gang members.  Spoiler comes to his aid but is still hurting. 

Things get worse when Red Robin reveals himself with an attack against Robin.
name: Search For A Hero, Part 3: Chaos In A Bottle

description:
The secret Jedi Covenant has one leader, but it isn't the devoted Jedi seer, Lady Krynda Draay . . .

As Padawan Zayne Carrick struggles to clear his name, the Masters who framed him for murder are finding the ideals they have worked so hard to protect are crumbling. They have been deceived by a trusted advisor whose hostile takeover will pit the Jedi Knights against one another-true Jedi of the Order vs. the misguided Jedi of the Covenant!
name: Vindication, Part 3

volume.name: Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic

description:
FIGHTMASTER AND DROP KICK RETURN!

They’re back from the future to alter the past – can Invincible stop them – or will he be lost in the time stream forever? Also in this issue: Kid Omni-Man saves the day.

When Lord Tadakazu died without leaving an heir, the Shogun himself took responsibility for dividing the lord's holdings. Mysteriously, an entire fortress was given to Lord Otomo, a rival of Tadakazu, with the provision that he personally take possession of the structure.


When Usagi discovers that the Neko ninja plan to attack Lord Otomo, the rabbit ronin believes this strange gift may be part of a plot to assassinate the lord. Yet no ninja assault can compare to the surprise that awaits Otomo within the walls of his old enemy's fortress.
name: The Fortress

description: So why did Celeste marry a senile old super-hero? Find out this issue, as the facts surrounding the courtship and marriage of Colonel Comet and Celeste are finally revealed!
name: Tough Love

description: The shadows of the city grow thick with ninja blades. The Hand is back in New York, on the hunt for something as yet unknown...but the enigmatic new Lady Bullseye is in league with them, and whatever they're after can't be good news for Daredevil and his friends. The first chapter of "Broken Hand" begins here -- featuring Iron Fist, the Black Tarantula, and more!
name: Lady Bullseye, Part Two
